text:
 Open the napkin and place it down in front of you.  Fold the top, right corner down to the middle.  Fold the bottom, left corner up to the middle.  Holding the top right triangle in the middle:Lift the napkin up. The other triangle will open up. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1b\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1b\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Flip the napkin over and place it back down. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/2b\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/2b\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Still holding the napkin, fold it to the bottom of the top triangle. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/fb\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/fb\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-760px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Bring the triangle from underneath, out. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1e\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet4.jpg\/v4-460px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/1e\/Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet4.jpg\/v4-760px-Fold-a-Napkin-Into-a-Bishops-Mitre-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Flip the napkin over.  Fold the triangle on the right in half, right to left.  Lift the bottom triangle up, covering half of the folded triangle.  Flip the napkin over and fold the triangle on the right in half, right to left.  Fold the end of the triangle in a little bit.  Tuck the bit you have just folded behind the other triangle.  Gently put your fingers in the underside of the Bishops Mitre and open it up.  Place the Bishops Mitre on your table for a marvellous display.
